Titanic data description /Rdatasets/datasets.html (TitanicSurvival)

The first project is based on data collected on the Titanic disaster, and we are interested in the age and gender of the survivors and those who perished. According to our data we have a total of 1309 passengers, 843 males and 466 females. We only have the age information of 1046 passengers, 658 males and 388 females.



Now we're going to describe the distribution of ages in the people who survived and perished in the tragic event.



Now let's create a treemap with the information given by our data.

About my bachelor's degree project

My degree project in applied mathematics was based on the effects of introducing a delay $\tau$ in the system of differential equations that control the movement of a mobile plate of the MEMS model known as Comb-drive. $$ \begin{equation} \label{combsystem} \ddot{x} + \gamma\dot{x} + x - u = \frac{4\beta (v_0+G(\dot{x}_{\tau}-\dot{x}))^2x}{(1-x^2)^2}, \quad x \in ]-1,1[, \end{equation} $$ Where $G \in \mathbb{R} $, $$ \left. \begin{aligned} \dot{x_1} & = x_2\\ \dot{x_2} & = \frac{38.8539 \times 10^{-4} (2.5-50({x_{2\tau}}-x_2))^2x_1}{(1-x_1^2)^2} - 0.7297 x_2 - x_1 + 0.05 \end{aligned} \right \rbrace. $$ $x_1$ is the position and $x_2$ is the velocity.


In the next image it can be evidenced the effects of the delay $\tau$ in the solutions $x_1$ and $x_2$ of the system.
